# 08 — Hardware Standard

## DCC structure (approved — do not redesign)

Logic Board + Power Board + Radio Board in one enclosure. Gen2 may replace Power Board only.

Internal DCC links: SPI (Logic↔Radio, Logic↔Power via J_LP). No CAN inside DCC.

## Design principles

- Separate logic and power domains; document ground strategy and thermal paths.
- High-current: verified copper/busbar — not headline ratings alone.
- Protection coordination: fuse, switch limit, wiring, connector derating, software limits.
- Connector policy: approved families per `docs/002` / EDL (Deutsch DTM/DT/DTP) unless ADR changes.
- Prototype: test points for SWD, CAN, SPI, sense — without unsafe high-current exposure on production unit.

## Serviceability

Modular boards, replaceable Radio, BOARD_ID for Power revision detection.

## Qualification

Component records in `hardware/qualification/` before approved BOM.

## Scope

Create KiCad, schematics, PCB **only when work package explicitly requests**.

Reference (not frozen by this pack): `docs/002`, `docs/007`, `docs/008` DevKit gate (EDL-014).
